1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available.]

2
00:00:38,950 --> 00:00:40,750
Do Min-joon!

3
00:00:41,090 --> 00:00:43,100
Do Min-joon!

4
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:48,520
Do Min-joon!

5
00:00:52,210 --> 00:00:57,830
♫ If only you accept me ♫

6
00:00:58,540 --> 00:01:00,660
Do Min-joon!

7
00:00:59,540 --> 00:01:05,140
♫ If only I see you again ♫

8
00:01:06,780 --> 00:01:08,870
Do Min-joon!

9
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:12,380
♫ I will call your name ♫

10
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,950
Why are you yelling my name?

11
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:16,300
♫ in memories ♫

12
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:19,950
♫ and in pain ♫

13
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,200
Where have you been?

14
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,920
I took a walk for some fresh air.

15
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:35,750
♫ You're my destiny ♫

16
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:23,230
I was frightened to death!

17
00:01:23,230 --> 00:01:25,990
I thought you were gone.

18
00:01:25,990 --> 00:01:27,860
Where can I go?

19
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:30,730
It seems like you’ll be gone anytime.

20
00:01:30,730 --> 00:01:32,780
I won’t go.

21
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:36,270
I won’t leave you behind.

22
00:01:35,750 --> 00:01:39,759
♫ You're my everything ♫

23
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:38,390
I’ll stay here.

24
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:40,150
What do you mean?

25
00:01:39,759 --> 00:01:43,720
♫ I can do nothing but watch you ♫

26
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:42,440
I say I won’t leave you.

27
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:45,930
I’m not leaving in one month, or two.

28
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:50,740
♫ I call your name in silence ♫

29
00:01:45,930 --> 00:01:47,770
So

30
00:01:47,770 --> 00:01:49,960
don’t be insecure.

31
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:56,100
Will it be OK if you stay?

32
00:01:50,740 --> 00:02:05,730
♫ You're the one my love ♫

33
00:01:58,259 --> 00:02:00,210
It’s OK.

34
00:02:00,210 --> 00:02:04,620
Seriously?

35
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:09,729
♫ You're my delight of all ♫

36
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:16,450
♫ I love you more and more ♫

37
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,130
What’s wrong?

38
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,070
Let’s go.

39
00:02:47,070 --> 00:02:48,820
Where?

40
00:02:50,210 --> 00:02:53,600
Somewhere with walls and roof.

41
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:57,000
Somewhere dark and no one sees us.

42
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,280
Somewhere only you and I stay.

43
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:02,570
What?

44
00:03:02,570 --> 00:03:05,530
You heard it when I was arguing with Yun-jae?

45
00:03:12,190 --> 00:03:15,870
You should’ve told me there will be guests.

46
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:20,840
You won’t come if I told you.

47
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:26,220
It’s been a long time.

48
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:28,450
Yup, 7 years.

49
00:03:28,450 --> 00:03:32,370
It’s been 7 years since you confined me.

50
00:03:32,370 --> 00:03:33,540
What are you talking about?

51
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:35,730
Ms. Yang Min-ju has been grounded in an asylum

52
00:03:35,730 --> 00:03:40,590
in Yongsan-gu during the past 7 years.

53
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:44,300
Well, I see.

54
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:48,270
Mr. Lee Jae-kyung, you are suspected of

55
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:52,660
illegally confining Ms. Yang Min-ju.

56
00:03:52,660 --> 00:03:54,520
Me?

57
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,890
What have I done?

58
00:03:55,890 --> 00:03:58,880
You only hear what she says.

59
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:03,560
And obviously she’s mentally challenged.

60
00:04:05,350 --> 00:04:07,790
I’m not mad. I’m sane.

61
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:12,970
I thought you were having a good time abroad.

62
00:04:12,970 --> 00:04:16,110
I sent you abroad because you wanted to.

63
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:20,620
You’ve also been frightened, right, Hee-kyung?

64
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:22,900
But you must have misunderstood something.

65
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:25,510
I have nothing to do with this.

66
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:28,960
Jae-kyung, stop lying.

67
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:31,200
Lying?

68
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:33,760
Excuse me.

69
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,580
I have other errands to run.

70
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:40,010
Talk to my lawyer
if you need further investigation.

71
00:04:49,710 --> 00:04:50,610
What are you doing?

72
00:04:50,610 --> 00:04:52,100
You really don’t want to say something?

73
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:52,800
What?

74
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,540
About your wife, and Han Yoo-ra

75
00:04:55,540 --> 00:04:59,440
and Han-kyung.

76
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,950
You’re insane.

77
00:05:05,950 --> 00:05:09,830
I’ve got nothing to say to them.

78
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:13,110
That was my last attempt

79
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,840
to forgive you for

80
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,940
what you’ve done…

81
00:05:18,940 --> 00:05:19,650
What?

82
00:05:19,650 --> 00:05:25,340
I tried to give my beloved and respected brother

83
00:05:25,340 --> 00:05:27,280
a chance to defend himself.

84
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:30,380
I tried to understand you though it’s not easy.

85
00:05:31,830 --> 00:05:34,720
But I’ve given up now.

86
00:05:36,020 --> 00:05:38,030
My brother,

87
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:48,480
by the way, this is my last time

88
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:51,600
calling you “brother”.

89
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:54,310
From now on,

90
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,790
you are not my older brother anymore.

91
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:24,300
They… have only one room left.

92
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,530
That’s not true.

93
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:26,970
Next door is also available.

94
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:28,670
But there’s no heating in that room.

95
00:06:28,670 --> 00:06:30,370
I can’t sleep without heating.

96
00:06:30,370 --> 00:06:33,200
Then I’ll sleep there.

97
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,710
Why bother?

98
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:40,560
We are in a dilemma now.

99
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,930
Let’s just sleep here.

100
00:06:41,930 --> 00:06:45,050
Dilemma is too big a word…

101
00:06:45,050 --> 00:06:47,070
I’m warning you.

102
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:49,530
No kissing!

103
00:06:49,530 --> 00:06:50,850
Period.

104
00:06:50,850 --> 00:06:53,150
True that I used to dream to be a nurse,

105
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:55,670
but nursing is really exhausting.

106
00:06:55,670 --> 00:06:57,680
What are you talking about?

107
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,200
I don’t plan to.

108
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:01,090
You can’t promise me things you’re not sure of.

109
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:04,550
That’s not “things I’m not sure of”.

110
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:07,230
I don’t want to do that from the beginning.

111
00:07:07,230 --> 00:07:09,420
You’re sure?

112
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:12,200
Then try lying on the bed at ease.

113
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:16,930
What’s that face?

114
00:07:16,930 --> 00:07:18,480
Face?

115
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,870
You’re blushing.

116
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:25,030
Me?

117
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:26,350
Even your ears turn red.

118
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:28,810
Well, it’s hot here.

119
00:07:28,810 --> 00:07:30,430
Hot?

120
00:07:30,430 --> 00:07:32,810
I don’t feel hot.

121
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:35,970
Well, hot it is.

122
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:37,820
I’m lying down.

123
00:07:37,820 --> 00:07:39,350
What?

124
00:07:42,980 --> 00:07:44,600
You don’t want to sleep?

125
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,590
Of course I do.

126
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:14,880
That was not a dream, was it?

127
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:18,160
You offered your arm to be my pillow.

128
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,310
Don’t know.

129
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:23,270
And you even kissed me.

130
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:25,450
You kissed me!

131
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,650
So we did kiss?

132
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:29,760
That was our first kiss.

133
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:34,620
I’m sleepy.

134
00:08:34,620 --> 00:08:36,500
Turn off the light.

135
00:08:37,929 --> 00:08:41,350
That’s one good thing about dating an alien.

136
00:08:56,030 --> 00:08:57,700
Move way.

137
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:03,550
Why?

138
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:05,800
Can’t turn off the light with your superpower?

139
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:08,140
I’m not in a good state today.

140
00:09:08,910 --> 00:09:11,010
I see. Come here.

141
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:19,670
Lady, you’re being too explicit, aren’t you?

142
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:22,380
Don’t tell me you’d do this to other men.

143
00:09:22,380 --> 00:09:23,710
Tut.

144
00:09:26,890 --> 00:09:28,800
Say it again.

145
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,330
What?

146
00:09:30,330 --> 00:09:32,250
What you said just now.

147
00:09:32,250 --> 00:09:33,740
What I said?

148
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:36,560
You are a lady. You should behave yourself…

149
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:39,650
That’s it. Cute, cute

150
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:40,890
Say it one more time.

151
00:09:40,890 --> 00:09:43,690
-Yoho.
-Yoho?

152
00:09:43,690 --> 00:09:45,620
-Tut.
-Tut.

153
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,400
Say that again.

154
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,930
You say it then. Go on.

155
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:52,470
OK. Fine. I’ll stop.

156
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,010
You are a lady…

157
00:10:00,450 --> 00:10:03,980
Where’s he? Not even picking up my phone?

158
00:10:14,930 --> 00:10:18,650
Hundreds of years have passed.

159
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:23,390
Not a single moment has ever stayed for me.

160
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:29,380
Now I know what matters is not how long you live

161
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:38,780
but who you’ve been living with.

162
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:46,160
All I want is to spend the rest of my life with her.

163
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:05,660
[My Love from the Star Record 18]

164
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:22,070
Get up. Time for breakfast.

165
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:30,120
Make me float.

166
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,350
What?

167
00:11:31,350 --> 00:11:33,190
Like you did

168
00:11:33,190 --> 00:11:37,380
when I was in an outdoor filming, remember?

169
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:39,870
I want to see the sink next time I open my eyes.

170
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:42,690
Stop rambling. Get up.

171
00:11:45,060 --> 00:11:49,390
I was panicking at that time.

172
00:11:49,390 --> 00:11:52,530
But then I just felt amazing.

173
00:11:52,530 --> 00:11:56,920
Just let me float one more time, will you?

174
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:01,820
Well, I can do that.

175
00:12:02,540 --> 00:12:04,880
Then do it.

176
00:12:13,390 --> 00:12:15,230
Are you trying?

177
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,040
How much do you weigh?

178
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,270
Does it matter?

179
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:21,760
You made it last time.

180
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:31,800
I’m floating! I’m floating!

181
00:12:34,710 --> 00:12:36,470
That’s it?

182
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:38,490
Can I float higher?

183
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,350
You can’t. I can tell from you face.

184
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:45,710
Because I just woke up.

185
00:12:46,590 --> 00:12:47,900
OK.

186
00:12:49,660 --> 00:12:52,420
My bad. I should not push you that hard.

187
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:57,160
I should just walk on my own foot.

188
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,360
Don’t care about that.

189
00:13:12,420 --> 00:13:14,540
Sit here.

190
00:13:14,540 --> 00:13:16,830
Anything I can do to help?

191
00:13:18,010 --> 00:13:18,900
All done.

192
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:21,110
Not the food.

193
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:23,630
I’m talking about your superpower.

194
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:25,630
But you did float up.

195
00:13:25,630 --> 00:13:27,510
For a very short time.

196
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:29,360
And you seemed to be exhausting your strength.

197
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,750
Do you need some invigorator?

198
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:32,090
Will it work on you?

199
00:13:32,090 --> 00:13:33,470
Maybe ginseng is better?

200
00:13:33,470 --> 00:13:37,100
I’ve told you. It’s all because I just woke up.

201
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:38,440
And I was tired yesterday.

202
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:41,960
But you’ve done nothing yesterday.

203
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:44,330
You couldn’t even turn off the light.

204
00:13:44,330 --> 00:13:47,150
We’re counting on your superpower in the future.

205
00:13:47,150 --> 00:13:49,290
What should we do now?

206
00:13:49,290 --> 00:13:51,710
This conversation upsets me.

207
00:13:51,710 --> 00:13:54,010
No, no, no. Don’t be upset.

208
00:13:54,010 --> 00:13:55,730
We can’t have it all, can we?

209
00:13:55,730 --> 00:13:58,240
You must have been nervous. That’s nothing.

210
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:00,670
Don’t be upset, Do Min-joon.

211
00:14:00,670 --> 00:14:02,090
You can do it!

212
00:14:02,090 --> 00:14:03,760
Just push it a little bit.

213
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:06,360
Stop this!

214
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:08,900
Stop this!

215
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:12,200
-Please.
-Things will get better.

216
00:14:14,930 --> 00:14:17,910
Will that continue, or…

217
00:14:17,910 --> 00:14:18,860
I’m just curious.

218
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:21,780
It’s fun, and suddenly it…

219
00:14:28,150 --> 00:14:29,750
Cheon Song-yi, you…

220
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:32,100
Where have you been? What took you so long?

221
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,960
I was… acting in the film.

222
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,170
Nonsense.

223
00:14:36,170 --> 00:14:38,430
I checked the film’s schedule!

224
00:14:38,430 --> 00:14:41,570
You didn’t have a scene yesterday.

225
00:14:41,570 --> 00:14:43,150
Mr. Do, tell me.

226
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:47,120
You know her schedule the best.

227
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:50,920
Don’t tell me you two…

228
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:54,080
took a trip together last night.

229
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,680
Mrs. Cheon, I…

230
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,560
Blame me if you want.

231
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,020
I proposed it.

232
00:14:59,020 --> 00:15:01,050
It’s not about who proposed it.

233
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:05,200
You went to a trip anyway, right.

234
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:08,300
You may be used to American custom,

235
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:10,750
but my daughter should not be that open.

236
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:13,810
You took out a girl without permission?

237
00:15:13,810 --> 00:15:14,820
I’m sorry.

238
00:15:14,820 --> 00:15:18,250
Sorry? What are you sorry for?

239
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,960
Ms. Cheon Song-yi, tell us.

240
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:24,700
Did Do Min-joon forced you to go with him?

241
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:28,000
No, it’s the other way around.

242
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,510
Hear that?

243
00:15:29,510 --> 00:15:31,990
Then tell me, Mr. Do,

244
00:15:31,990 --> 00:15:35,150
will you marry my daughter?

245
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,160
What are you talking about?

246
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:37,980
Why?

247
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:39,690
Silent treatment?

248
00:15:39,690 --> 00:15:43,790
You take a girl you won’t marry to a trip?

249
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:49,330
Please tell your son to behave himself.

250
00:15:49,330 --> 00:15:51,140
It’s inappropriate for a man

251
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:53,170
to have no plan for his future.

252
00:15:53,170 --> 00:15:56,340
My son behaves very well.

253
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:58,660
He didn’t even have a girlfriend

254
00:15:58,660 --> 00:16:01,550
before Ms. Cheon.

255
00:16:01,550 --> 00:16:02,760
My boy is innocent.

256
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:05,710
Your daughter must have

257
00:16:05,710 --> 00:16:08,240
seduced him to that

258
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:11,400
My daughter? How dare you?

259
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,400
Hey, did you seduce him?

260
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:18,350
Well, you can say that.

261
00:16:20,090 --> 00:16:21,640
No.

262
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,410
It takes two to tango.

263
00:16:23,410 --> 00:16:26,900
You can't clap with one hand.

264
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:28,980
She’s not the only one to be blamed.

265
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:30,540
And

266
00:16:30,540 --> 00:16:33,700
I can understand why you

267
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:37,210
blame the man.

268
00:16:37,210 --> 00:16:40,550
I am terribly sorry.

269
00:16:40,550 --> 00:16:45,260
How old is your son?

270
00:16:50,690 --> 00:16:53,170
You’ve decided to stay?

271
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:54,650
Yes.

272
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:58,440
I don’t get it.

273
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:00,880
What can I do?

274
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:03,960
You stay even though you may die.

275
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:08,339
But think about it. No one’s immortal.

276
00:17:08,339 --> 00:17:10,950
That’s life.

277
00:17:10,950 --> 00:17:13,310
I’ll come around to it.

278
00:17:15,220 --> 00:17:20,200
Is everything going well with you?

279
00:17:25,540 --> 00:17:26,970
Well…

280
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:28,470
What?

281
